<h2>Metadata</h2>
    <p>Metadata is data&nbsp;about&nbsp;data.Metadata is a kind of data, which is an abstraction of a data.It mainly describes the type information of data.</p>
    <p>Normal source file (c or c++ language) can be compiled into binary file in the compiler. When compiling, the compiler only extracts the information required for CPU execution and ignores the type information of data. For example a pointer, if you just look at the binary code or assembly code after compilation, you cannot tell if it is of integer type or char type.If it is a pointer to string, you cannot tell the length of the string either. This type information belongs to metadata information we mentioned.</p>
